class  UdpDemultiplexer
 This class serves as a de-multiplexer for packets received via local UDP endpoints. The packets are separated according to their remote IP address and/or port number. So, clients using this class can register a callback for UDP traffic flowing from a remote to a local endpoint. In general, it is not allow to have more than one thread listening on the same UDP socket. So, instances of this class have an own thread that receives UDP packets and distributes them via the registered callbacks. More...

float ibeo::common::sdk::normalizeRadians ( float  angleInRad)
inline

Normalize the given angle.

Normalizes an angle given in radians by adding or subtracting an integer multiple of 2*pi so that the resulting angle is in the half-open interval (-pi,+pi]. The current implementation takes O(1) time, i.e. the time of execution has a fixed upper boundary independend from the angle.

Parameters
[in]angleInRadAngle to be normalized given in rad.
Returns
The normalized angle in (-pi, +pi].

uint16_t ibeo::common::sdk::readLE16 ( const uint8_t *&  buf,
BitNumber &  firstBitToRead,
const int  nbOfDataBits 
)

Read a value val with nbOfDataBits (between 9 and 16) bits from the given buffer buf starting at bit firstBitToRead inside the buffer.

If not all bits to be read available inside the byte pointed to by buf, the rest of the bits will be read from the next byte. Starting with the least significant bit.

Parameters
[in,out]bufPointer to the position of the byte where to read the first bit from. On exit this variable will point to the position inside of the buffer where to read the next bit from after this read operation.
[in,out]firstBitToReadId of the first bit to be read from the buffer. On exit this variable will hold the id of the next bit to be read from after this read operation.
[in]nbOfDataBitsThe number of bits to be read from the buffer buf. These bits are returned. nbOfDataBits must between 9 and 16.
Returns
A byte that contains the read bits. Starting with the least significant bit.
uint8_t ibeo::common::sdk::readLE8 ( const uint8_t *&  buf,
BitNumber &  firstBitToRead,
const int  nbOfDataBits 
)

Read a value val with nbOfDataBits (between 1 and 8) bits from the given buffer buf starting at bit firstBitToRead inside the buffer.

If not all bits to be read available inside the byte pointed to by buf, the rest of the bits will be read from the next byte. Starting with the least significant bit.

Parameters
[in,out]bufPointer to the position of the byte where to read the first bit from. On exit this variable will point to the position inside of the buffer where to read the next bit from after this read operation.
[in,out]firstBitToReadId of the first bit to be read from the buffer. On exit this variable will hold the id of the next bit to be read from after this read operation.
[in]nbOfDataBitsThe number of bits to be read from the buffer buf. These bits are returned. nbOfDataBits must between 1 and 8.
Returns
A byte that contains the read bits. Starting with the least significant bit.

void ibeo::common::sdk::writeLE ( uint8_t *&  buf,
BitNumber &  firstBitToWrite,
uint8_t  val,
const int  nbOfDataBits 
)

Write a value val with nbOfDataBits (between 1 and 8) bits to the given buffer buf starting at bit firstBitToWrite.

If not all given bits fit into the byte pointed to by buf, the rest of the bits will be written into the next byte. Starting with the least significant bit.

Parameters
[in,out]bufPointer to the position of the byte where to write the first bit of val into. On exit this variable will point to the position inside of the buffer where to write from the next bit after this write operation.
[in,out]firstBitToWriteId of the first bit to be (over)written in the buffer. On exit this variable will hold the id of the next bit to be written to after this write operation.
[in]valVariable that contains the bit to be written into the buffer buf.
[in]nbOfDataBitsThe number of bits to be written into the buffer buf. These bits are provided in the parameter val. Starting with the least significant bit. nbOfDataBits must between 1 and 8.
void ibeo::common::sdk::writeLE ( uint8_t *&  buf,
BitNumber &  firstBitToWrite,
const uint16_t  val,
const int  nbOfDataBits 
)

Write a value val with nbOfDataBits (between 9 and 16) bits to the given buffer buf starting at bit firstBitToWrite.

If not all given bits fit into the byte pointed to by buf, the rest of the bits will be written into the next byte. Starting with the least significant bit.

Parameters
[in,out]bufPointer to the position of the byte where to write the first bit of val into. On exit this variable will point to the position inside of the buffer where to write from the next bit after this write operation.
[in,out]firstBitToWriteId of the first bit to be (over)written in the buffer. On exit this variable will hold the id of the next bit to be written to after this write operation.
[in]valVariable that contains the bit to be written into the buffer buf.
[in]nbOfDataBitsThe number of bits to be written into the buffer buf. These bits are provided in the parameter val. Starting with the least significant bit. nbOfDataBits must between 9 and 16.
